"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909401","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>Data on funding for HIV testing is not collected centrally. HIV testing services are commissioned by local authorities through the ring fenced public health grant. Most testing takes place in sexual health services and over a million people were tested for HIV in these services in 2016. This testing identified 2,358 new HIV diagnoses, a positivity rate of 0.2%. In addition, all health services are expected to test for HIV opportunistically when an individual presents with symptoms which may be indicative of HIV.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-04T13:57:42.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909401/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909401/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-22","HIV Infection: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what funding from the public purse has been allocated to support the provision of routine HIV testing at NHS Trusts.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","146944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909402","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-06-04","<p>All meetings on official business are declared in the transparency returns and can be found on the GOV.UK page: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-exiting-the-european-union&amp;publication_type=transparency-data.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","146738 ; 146739 ; 146816 ; 146817 ; 146818 ; 146819 ; 146840 ; 146841 ; 146842","2018-06-04T13:47:07.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909402/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909402/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-05-22","Shanker Singham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department was made aware of what was discussed at the meetings held between Steve Baker and Shanker Singham that have taken place since July 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","146740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909403","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-04","<p>The new timetable across Southern commenced on Sunday 20 May and there have been wholly unsatisfactory levels of disruption on those rail services since then. A combination of delayed Network Rail infrastructure works and reduced time to plan a modified timetable meant that the new timetable was finalised much too late to permit adequate logistical planning for the timetable changes. I am determined both that the problems are dealt with as quickly as possible, and that this is not repeated in the future.</p><p> </p><p>We have been in regular contact with the leadership of Network Rail and GTR since the new timetable was introduced, and I and the Secretary of State continue to monitor the situation closely. We are speaking to those involved on a daily basis and we have insisted that both organisations put whatever resource they need to into resolving the situation, and in making sure that there is proper leadership of the recovery effort.</p><p> </p><p>Once these problems are resolved, we will have a much better service for passengers. That is small comfort at the moment when things are not working as they should, but once we are through this difficult period we will have a better railway, with more frequent and better connected journeys for passengers across the Southern Metro routes, including the Wimbledon loop and the West London line.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-04T15:57:47.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909403/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909403/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-22","Southern Rail: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with representatives of Southern Rail on the effect of the May 2018 timetable changes on commuters travelling across south west London.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","146945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909404","Department for International Trade","false","2018-06-04","<p>I refer the Hon. Member for Hemsworth to the answer I gave him on 31 May 2017, UIN 146742 &amp; 146743.</p><p> </p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-06-04T10:13:54.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909404/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909404/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-22","Shanker Singham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many meetings Crawford Falconer, Chief Trade Negotiation Adviser and Second Permanent Secretary for the Department for International Trade, has had with the policy adviser Shanker Singham since July 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","146741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909405","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-31","<p>The Chief Trade Negotiation Adviser has had no official meetings with Shanker Singham. All meetings on official business are declared in the transparency returns and can be found on the gov.uk page:</p><p><br>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade&amp;publication_type=transparency-data</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","146743","2018-05-31T10:04:37.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909405/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909405/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-22","Shanker Singham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether his Department was made aware of the meetings that Crawford Falconer has had with the policy adviser Shanker Singham since July 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","146742"
