"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909413","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","<p>The 2019 loan charge is targeted at artificial schemes where earnings were paid in the form of non-repayable loans made by an offshore third party.</p><p> </p><p>It is unfair to ordinary taxpayers to let anybody benefit from contrived tax avoidance of this sort, and that is why this government has taken action to ensure that everybody pays the taxes they owe.</p><p> </p><p>Given the specific targeting of these contrived tax avoidance schemes, the 2019 loan charge is not expected to have significant effects on the economy or the NHS.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-04T15:04:26.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909413/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909413/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-22","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the (a) economy and (b) NHS of the 2019 Loan Charge.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","146978"
