"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909465","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Government will monitor the impact of the various elements of the whiplash reform programme following implementation. This includes both the measures being taken forward in the Civil Liability Bill and the supplementary measures to increase the small claims limit for personal injury claims which require secondary legislation.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-04T14:06:55.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909465/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909465/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-22","Personal Injury: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he plans to monitor the effect of increases in the small claims limit for personal injury claims on (a) the judiciary, (b) the courts and (c) claimants.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","146962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909466","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-04","<p>Data on the total value of council tax exemptions is not collected by the Department.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","146888 ; 146889","2018-06-04T11:31:26.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909466/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909466/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-22","Council Tax: Ministers of Religion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the total value of the class H council tax exemption was in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","146890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909467","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-29","<p>The Government is carrying out a post-implementation review of Part 2 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 this year and plans to publish its report by the end of this year.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-29T16:24:05.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909467/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909467/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-22","Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to conduct a post-implementation review of part 2 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","146963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909468","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-04","<p>The government intends to publish the post-implementation review of Part 2 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 by the end 2018.</p><p>It intends to implement all elements of the whiplash reform programme as a package by April 2019, including both the measures in the Civil Liability Bill and supplementary measures to increase the small claims limit for personal injury claims which require secondary legislation.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-04T14:07:02.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909468/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909468/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-22","Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will delay any increase in the small claims limit for personal injury claims until completion of a post-implementation review of part 2 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","146964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909469","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department does not collect this information. Ability to drive is not an eligibility condition for the higher rate mobility component of Disability Living Allowance. Eligibility is based, for example, on limitations in someone’s ability to freely manoeuvre outdoors without guidance or supervision or whether someone is unable or virtually unable to walk. People in receipt of the higher rate mobility component who wish to join the Motability scheme and lease a vehicle but who cannot drive can nominate a named driver to drive their Motability car.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-04T16:40:39.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909469/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909469/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-22","Disability Living Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the proportion of parents of children who receive the higher rate disability living allowance mobility component who are not qualified to drive.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","146909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909470","Department for Education","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Government expects all schools to ensure that the teaching of Relationships and Sex Education (RSE) is inclusive of the needs of all pupils, whatever their developing sexuality or identity, and is delivered in an age-appropriate way. All schools are required to comply with the Equality Act 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Following provisions in the Children and Social Work Act 2017, the Government is making Relationships Education at primary school and RSE at secondary school mandatory through regulations. To support decisions on the content of these subjects the Department recently conducted an engagement exercise with a wide range of expert stakeholders, including LGBT groups, as well as a public call for evidence. As part of this exercise, officials also met their counterparts from the Welsh Government.</p><p> </p><p>Using the evidence gathered during this process, the Government is developing the regulations and accompanying statutory guidance for these subjects. They will then be subject to public consultation followed by a debate on the regulations in Parliament.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-04T07:48:05.96Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909470/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909470/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-22","Sex and Relationship Education: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will hold discussions with his Welsh counterpart on the merits of including LGBTQI+ inclusive sex and relationships education in schools in England.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","146971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909471","Department for Education","false","2018-06-04","<p>The government fully recognises the important economic and cultural contribution that EU and international students make to the UK’s higher education sector. We want that contribution to continue and we are confident – given the world class quality of our higher education sector – that it will. We welcome international students and there continues to be no limit on the number who can come here to study, nor any plans to limit any institution’s ability to recruit international students from outside the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The UK remains a highly attractive destination for non-EU students, with their numbers remaining at record highs – over 170,000 non-EU entrants to UK higher education institutions (HEIs) for the seventh year running. We actively promote study in the UK through the GREAT Campaign and to over 100 countries through the British Council. To encourage ambition across the sector, the government also set an aspiration to increase education exports (up to 60% of which is comprised of international students at UK HEIs) to £30 billion by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>To help inform decisions on the future migration system, the government has commissioned the independent Migration Advisory Committee to provide an objective assessment of the impact of EU and non-EU international students by September 2018. This has provided an important opportunity for the sector to share views and evidence.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-06-04T05:54:19.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909471/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909471/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-22","Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has to increase the number of overseas students studying in UK universities over the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","146912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909472","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department has not made the estimates requested, however Departmental statisticians are currently developing these statistics further to look at destinations into employment following a sanction.</p><p> </p><p>The Department also publishes experimental statistics on claimants receiving a benefit sanction which currently show information on the number and proportion of individuals receiving sanctions, including time spent on benefits following the sanction. These figures can be found in our quarterly Benefit Sanction Statistics available at the following link: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/710021/benefit-sanctions-statistics-to-january-2018.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/710021/benefit-sanctions-statistics-to-january-2018.pdf</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-06-04T11:01:29.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909472/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909472/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-22","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has made an estimate of the (a) number and (b) proportion of benefit claimants who have been sanctioned and subsequently find employment at (i) 3 months, (ii) 6 months and (iii) 12 months after having been sanctioned.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","146913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909473","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-04","<p>The UK leads the world in our long-term support for comprehensive sexual and reproductive health and rights (SRHR) including for family planning.</p><p>In 2012 the UK committed to spend an average of £180m a year on family planning (FP) to 2020. Using internationally-agreed methodology (FP2020, Family Planning global partnership), since then DFID has spent a total of at least £910 million on Family Planning programmes between 2012/13 – 2016/17, which is an average of approximately £184 million each year. This includes both bilateral and core multilateral contributions to organisations such as UNFPA, WHO, World Bank &amp; Global Fund for Aids, Tuberculosis Malaria. DFID are currently the second largest global bilateral donor for family planning in developing countries and have met the 2012 commitment.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-04T15:53:40.57Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909473/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909473/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-22","Developing Countries: Family Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department spent on supporting birth control programmes in developing countries in (a) total and (b) each year for the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","146914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909474","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-29","<p>We intend to assess the impact of Bereavement Support Payment once sufficient evidence is available to assess all aspects of the policy.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-05-29T10:49:24.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909474/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909474/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-22","Bereavement Support Payment Regulations 2017","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions what assessment the Government has made of the effectiveness of the Bereavement Support Payments Regulation 2017.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","146811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909475","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-29","<p>Initially we will be investing extra funds into the reform to bereavement benefits and significant savings are not anticipated during the course of this Parliament.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-05-29T10:49:37.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909475/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909475/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-22","Bereavement Support Payment Regulations 2017","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the savings to the Exchequer since the introduction of the Bereavement Support Payment Regulations 2017.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","146812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909476","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-29","<p>The Department publishes quarterly Bereavement Support Payment statistics that show the volume of claims being paid broken down by standard rate and higher rate payments. Claimants with dependent children and entitled to Child Benefit, or who were pregnant, when their husband, wife or civil partner died will get the higher rate. The latest statistics are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dwp-benefits-statistical-summaries-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/dwp-benefits-statistical-summaries-2018</a>.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-05-29T10:49:49.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909476/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909476/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-22","Bereavement Support Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families have claimed bereavement support since 6 April 2017.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","146813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909477","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-31","<p>​We have raised the detention of Taner Kilic with the Turkish Government at all levels. Most recently the Prime Minister discussed the case with President Erdogan during his recent visit to the UK. We urge Turkey to ensure Mr Kilic's release from pre-trial detention and to bring his case to a transparent, fair conclusion.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-05-31T13:27:57.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909477/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909477/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-22","Taner Kılıç","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he raised the case of the chair of Amnesty International Turkey, Taner Kılıç, during the recent visit of President Erdogan to the UK.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","146977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909478","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>Information on the In-Country leave to remain work in progress is available in our published transparency data at the link below. See tab InC_03.</p><p>Family and private life applications are included in the HR/Complex category but this also includes outside of the rules applications.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:57:08.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909478/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909478/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many leave to remain (family and private life) applications are currently pending.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909479","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>Information on processing times for In-Country leave to remain applications is available in our published transparency data at the link below. See tab InC_05.</p><p>Family and private life applications are included in the Non-Straightforward Workable category but this also includes outside of the rules applications.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:54:55.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909479/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909479/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what is the average duration is for processing a leave to remain (family and private life category) application.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909480","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-04","<p>As stated in the Government’s 25 Year Environment Plan we are committed to supporting comprehensive and frequent waste and recycling collections, and want to ensure that products are recycled as much as possible, returning high quality materials back to the economy. We will set out plans to increase recycling in the Resources and Waste Strategy to be published later this year. This will include taking forward our commitment in the Litter Strategy to work with stakeholders to explore how cost‑sharing arrangements (including recycling credits) for waste and recycling can work most effectively, especially in areas of two-tier authorities.</p><p> </p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-06-04T12:40:40.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909480/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909480/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-22","Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to increase the amount of recycling of materials; if he will protect the level of recycling credits for local government; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","146716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909481","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>Information on processing times for In-Country leave to remain applications is available in our published transparency data at the link below. See tab InC_05.</p><p>Family and private life applications are included in the Non-Straightforward Workable category but this also includes outside of the rules applications.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-february-2018</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:55:34.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909481/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909481/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average duration of processing leave to remain (family and private life category) applications has been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909482","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>The Home Office does not currently have a published service standard for family and private life applications but endeavours to determine what are often complex applications as soon as possible.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:52:43.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909482/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909482/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether his Department applies service standards for processing leave to remain (family and private life) applications.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909483","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>The information to be provided for a death registration is prescribed in regulations made under the Births and Deaths Registration Act 1953. There are no plans to amend legislation to include the names of any dependent children of the deceased.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:31:44.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909483/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909483/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ensure that dependent children are included on the register of death of a parent.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","146814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909484","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>The Home Office receives regular contact from MPs representing their constituents, including queries about their constituents’ family and human rights applications.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:48:55.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909484/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909484/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what representations his Department has received from hon. Members and civil society organisations on implementing service standards for leave to remain (family and private life) applications.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909485","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>An acknowledgement letter is despatched to the applicant when their family and private life application is input onto our caseworking system. This letter advises that no service standard applies but that the application will be completed as soon as possible.</p><p>After the initial acknowledgement, caseworkers will contact individuals where further information or evidence is required to consider and progress their application, but do not provide running updates on the status of applications in progress.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-30T13:46:03.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909485/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909485/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the guidelines for staff processing leave to remain (family and private life) applications on updating applicants of the status of that application are.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909486","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>We will consider requests to expedite family and private life applications in the most serious circumstances, such as serious family illness or bereavement abroad or other exceptionally compassionate circumstances, if such requests are supported by documentary evidence.</p><p>The criteria against which we will expedite is under constant review.</p><p>The Home Office receives requests from MPs and their offices for the expediting of their constituents’ family and human rights applications. Such requests are considered as a priority. I am not aware of any correspondence the Home Office has had recently with civil society organisations about our expedite criteria.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","146769 ; 146770","2018-05-30T13:42:51.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909486/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909486/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on what grounds can people applying for leave to remain (family and private life) expedite that request.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909487","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>We will consider requests to expedite family and private life applications in the most serious circumstances, such as serious family illness or bereavement abroad or other exceptionally compassionate circumstances, if such requests are supported by documentary evidence.</p><p>The criteria against which we will expedite is under constant review.</p><p>The Home Office receives requests from MPs and their offices for the expediting of their constituents’ family and human rights applications. Such requests are considered as a priority. I am not aware of any correspondence the Home Office has had recently with civil society organisations about our expedite criteria.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","146768 ; 146770","2018-05-30T13:42:51.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909487/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909487/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether he plans to review the grounds for people applying for leave to remain (family and private life) to be able to expedite that request.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909488","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>We will consider requests to expedite family and private life applications in the most serious circumstances, such as serious family illness or bereavement abroad or other exceptionally compassionate circumstances, if such requests are supported by documentary evidence.</p><p>The criteria against which we will expedite is under constant review.</p><p>The Home Office receives requests from MPs and their offices for the expediting of their constituents’ family and human rights applications. Such requests are considered as a priority. I am not aware of any correspondence the Home Office has had recently with civil society organisations about our expedite criteria.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","146768 ; 146769","2018-05-30T13:42:51.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909488/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909488/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-22","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether he has received representations from (a) hon. Members and (b) civil society organisations on reviewing the grounds on which people applying for leave to remain (family and private life) can expedite their request.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","146770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909489","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-30","<p>The Government is undertaking a wide range of analysis in support of our EU exit negotiations and preparations.</p><p>The analysis considers the merits of existing trade structures such as the Pan Euro Mediterranean Convention on Rules of Origin. However, this work is ongoing and the Government has not yet determined what its final approach will be.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-05-30T14:31:20.76Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909489/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909489/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-22","Origin Marking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to retain membership of Regional Convention on Pan-Euro-Mediterranean Preferential Rules of Origin after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Antoinette Sandbach","Eddisbury","Antoinette Sandbach","146932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909490","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Government has committed in our 25 Year Environment Plan and Clean Growth Strategy to reforming our producer responsibility systems (including the packaging waste regulations) to incentivise producers to take greater responsibility for the environmental impacts of their products. This will look at all aspects of the packaging producer responsibility regime, including mechanisms to incentivise better design and encourage the greater use of recycled material, as well as the funding of collections within the system.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State has had discussions with the Waste &amp; Resources Action Programme, the Industry Council for Packaging &amp; the Environment and the Advisory Committee on Packaging as representatives of industry to hear their views on reforming the packaging producer responsibility system, including incentivising the use of recycled content.</p><p> </p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-06-04T12:47:31.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909490/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909490/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-22","Packaging: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with industry on raising the level of recycled materials in packaging recovery notes.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","146717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909491","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-06-04","<p>All meetings on official business are declared in the transparency returns and can be found on the GOV.UK page: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-exiting-the-european-union&amp;publication_type=transparency-data.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","146738 ; 146739 ; 146740 ; 146817 ; 146818 ; 146819 ; 146840 ; 146841 ; 146842","2018-06-04T13:47:07.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909491/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909491/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-05-22","Shanker Singham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what meetings the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, the hon. Member for Wycombe, has had with Shanker Singham since June 2017; and what the purpose of those meetings was.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","146816"
